<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>出版物 |皮尤研究中心</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/publications/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Thu, 02 Jul 2026 02:04:09 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>大多数美国人支持禁止 16 岁以下儿童使用社交媒体</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/07/01/majority-of-americans-support-banning-social-media-for-kids-under-16/</link><description>在主要人口和党派群体中，支持禁止 16 岁以下儿童使用社交媒体的美国人多于反对者。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 01 Jul 2026 14:03:41 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/07/01/majority-of-americans-support-banning-social-media-for-kids-under-16/</guid></item><item><title>5% 的美国人表示他们曾经乘坐过无人驾驶汽车</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/07/01/5-of-americans-say-theyve-ridden-in-a-driverless-car/</link><description>无论他们以前是否乘坐过无人驾驶汽车，大多数美国人（71%）表示他们乘坐无人驾驶汽车不太舒服或根本不舒服。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 01 Jul 2026 13:48:41 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/07/01/5-of-americans-say-theyve-ridden-in-a-driverless-car/</guid></item><item><title>大约三分之一的美国民主党人喜欢被视为民主社会主义者的政治领导人</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/30/about-a-third-of-us-democrats-like-political-leaders-who-identify-as-democratic-socialists/</link><description>民主党人对民主社会主义者的看法也因种族、年龄、教育、收入和政治参与而有所不同。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 01 Jul 2026 02:12:02 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/30/about-a-third-of-us-democrats-like-political-leaders-who-identify-as-democratic-socialists/</guid></item><item><title>关于菲律宾宗教的 5 个事实</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/30/5-facts-about-religion-in-the-philippines/</link><description>几乎所有菲律宾人都信仰上帝，大多数人每天祈祷，92% 的人认为自己是基督徒，其中天主教徒占大多数。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 01 Jul 2026 01:57:02 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/30/5-facts-about-religion-in-the-philippines/</guid></item><item><title>哪些美国人最有可能与当地记者交谈过？</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/29/which-americans-are-most-likely-to-have-spoken-with-a-local-journalist/</link><description>大约四分之一的美国人曾与当地记者交谈过，教育程度、收入、种族和社区归属感与较高的互动率有关。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 29 Jun 2026 15:27:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/29/which-americans-are-most-likely-to-have-spoken-with-a-local-journalist/</guid></item><item><title>对于美国大多数都市区的年轻人来说，买房变得越来越困难</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/24/buying-a-home-has-gotten-harder-for-young-adults-in-most-us-metro-areas/</link><description>大约十分之九的 40 岁以下成年人表示，买房比他们的父母更难，因为房价和抵押贷款利率的上涨使拥有住房变得更加遥不可及。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 25 Jun 2026 02:08:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/24/buying-a-home-has-gotten-harder-for-young-adults-in-most-us-metro-areas/</guid></item><item><title>超过一半的州限制选举投注</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/23/more-than-half-of-states-restrict-betting-on-elections/</link><description>至少 16 个州的立法者今年出台了立法，以某种方式规范预测市场。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 24 Jun 2026 02:03:58 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/23/more-than-half-of-states-restrict-betting-on-elections/</guid></item><item><title>如果在调查过程中爆发战争会发生什么？</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/decoded/2026/06/23/what-happens-when-war-breaks-out-in-the-middle-of-a-survey/</link><description>研究人员利用美国和以色列对伊朗空袭期间进行的调查进行统计分析，追踪了全球对美国和各国经济看法的实时变化。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 23 Jun 2026 14:21:54 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/decoded/2026/06/23/what-happens-when-war-breaks-out-in-the-middle-of-a-survey/</guid></item><item><title>特朗普在国际上受到负面评价，更少人认为美国是可靠的合作伙伴</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/global/2026/06/23/trump-gets-negative-reviews-internationally-as-fewer-say-u-s-is-a-reliable-partner/</link><description>一项针对 36 个国家的调查发现，由于人们对美国外交政策和民主健康状况的担忧日益加剧，美国的支持率不断下降。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 23 Jun 2026 14:06:54 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/global/2026/06/23/trump-gets-negative-reviews-internationally-as-fewer-say-u-s-is-a-reliable-partner/</guid></item><item><title>许多美国人赞成在公立学校祈祷，但很少有人认为这应该是强制性的</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/22/many-americans-favor-prayer-in-public-schools-but-few-think-it-should-be-mandatory/</link><description>对于是否应该在公立学校教室展示《十诫》，美国人的看法几乎是平等的。但共和党人、白人福音派人士和美国老年人比其他群体更支持。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 23 Jun 2026 02:07:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/22/many-americans-favor-prayer-in-public-schools-but-few-think-it-should-be-mandatory/</guid></item></channel></rss>